  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nHi, in ERC721 token currently there is could be the only approved address for a unique token at the same time. There are some cases when it needed to approve more than one address. For example: `.crypto domain is ERC721 token and I want to allow manage this domain records to multiple users.\r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\n**Current implementation looks like this:**\r\n```\r\n    function _approve(address to, uint256 tokenId) private {\r\n        _tokenApprovals[tokenId] = to;\r\n        emit Approval(ownerOf(tokenId), to, tokenId);\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n\r\n**It might look like:**\r\n```\r\n    function _approve(address to, uint256 tokenId) private {\r\n        _tokenApprovals[tokenId][to] = true;\r\n        emit Approval(ownerOf(tokenId), to, tokenId);\r\n    }\r\n```",
